article.headline: UMKC 80, Centenary 75
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Quinton Day had 26 points Thursday to lead Missouri-Kansas City to an 80-75 win over Centenary. The Kangaroos (7-11, 2-0 Mid-Continent Conference) almost blew a 19-point second-half lead before holding off the Gents (7-11, 1-2). An inside basket by Alex Pledger with 14:38 left in the game put UMKC up 53-34, but Centenary rallied to pull within a point at 76-75 with 41 seconds remaining. The Kangaroos hit four free throws in the closing seconds for the final margin. UMKC went on a 20-6 run at the end of the first half to go into the break with a 43-27 lead. Offensive rebounding kept Centenary in the game, with the Gents leading that category 25-11. Tyrone Hamilton led Centenary with 24 points, Alexander Starr had 19 and Iman Shokouhizadeh added 10. Dee Ayuba had 20 points for the Kangaroos, and Pledger was a perfect 8-of-8 from the floor in scoring a career-high 19 points.
